                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The root rotter is standing in fungal terrain</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Fungal roots reach out to snag a nearby foe. An enemy within 30 feet of the root rotter takes @Damage[4d6[piercing]] damage and must attempt a @Check[reflex|dc:27] saving throw.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and becomes clumsy 1 with an unlimited duration. In addition, the creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained] (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Escape] DC 27) for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure but double damage. In addition, the creature is exposed to rotter infestation.</p>"
